properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 19 at 4:19AM AKST until February 20 at 5:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to 5 inches. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph. Visibility
to one half mile at times.

* WHERE...North of King Salmon.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 5 AM AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow and blowing snow are expected across
Bristol Bay as the next front approaches the region. Expect the
biggest impact to coastal areas from Dillingham to Goodnews Bay,
which could see sustained winds of 25 mph and visibility drop
to one half mile in blowing snow. Highest snow totals of 3 to 5
inches will be near Dillingham and New Stuyahok.
properties.instruction: Slow down and use caution while traveling.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 5 AM AKST THURSDAY NORTH OF KING SALMON
